    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-09-20T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-09-20T10:00:00-05:00" n="594"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d594">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/10146a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-09-20T11:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 20, 1937—11 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>394. Please inquire and report urgently any information you can obtain from
                    Foreign Office as to what the British Government proposes to do in respect to
                    notice of Japanese Admiral relating to bombing of Nanking on and after 21st
                        instant.<note n="31" xml:id="d594fn31">See telegram No. 728, September 19, 1
                        p.m., from the Consul General at Shanghai, <ref
                            target="frus1931-41v01#pg_499">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 499</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moore</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
